        <headline>Severe Thunderstorm Warning issued June 27 at 8:32PM CDT until June 27 at 9:00PM CDT by NWS Birmingham AL</headline>
        <description>SVRBMX

The National Weather Service in Birmingham has issued a

* Severe Thunderstorm Warning for...
Southwestern St. Clair County in central Alabama...

* Until 900 PM CDT.

* At 832 PM CDT, a severe thunderstorm was located over Coosa Island,
or near Pell City, and is nearly stationary.

HAZARD...60 mph wind gusts and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Expect damage to roofs, siding, and trees.

* Locations impacted include...
Pell City, Coosa Island, Logan Martin Lake, St. Clair County
Airport, Camp Winnataska, and Cropwell.
</description>
        <instruction>For your protection move to an interior room on the lowest floor of a
building.</instruction>
